# Architecture

## Snapshot model

Collectors produce partial data → aggregator builds one `Snapshot` → CLI/TUI/JSON render the same model.

```
cmd/bareai/          # main entry
internal/
  snapshot/          # shared types + aggregator
  collect/
    host/            # CPU, RAM, disk, load, OS
    gpu/             # NVIDIA / AMD / Apple adapters
    docker/          # Engine API: containers, images, volumes
    llm/             # discover + probe runtimes
  probe/             # HTTP health, /v1/models, one-hit chat/completions
  tui/               # Bubble Tea app (watch / browse)
  render/            # tables, human output
  doctor/            # optional findings (later phases)
```

## Collectors

- Each collector is optional and returns `(data, err)`; aggregator records skips
- GPU: NVML / nvidia-smi, ROCm, Apple Metal/sys — never hard-require one vendor
- LLM discovery: process + port + Docker name/image heuristics + HTTP probes
- Correlation: PID ↔ container ↔ GPU index ↔ endpoint URL

## Command surface (target)

```
bareai                  # launch TUI (default) or show help — decide in implementation
bareai status
bareai gpu
bareai llm
bareai docker
bareai inspect
bareai probe            # one-hit smoke test against discovered LLMs
bareai watch            # live TUI monitoring
bareai --json <cmd>
```

Prefer shared collector code; commands and TUI must not re-implement discovery.
